com.vmware.vcenter.hvc

Interface Links

  • All Superinterfaces:
    LinksTypes, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinksStub

    public interface Links
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, LinksTypes
    The Links interface provides methods to create, delete, get information, and list hybrid links between the local and foreign Platform Service Controller (PSC). Usage beyond VMware Cloud on AWS is not supported.

      • create

        java.lang.String create(LinksTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Creates a new hybrid link between the local and foreign PSC. Usage beyond VMware Cloud on AWS is not supported.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        spec - Specification for the new link to be created.
        Returns:
        The identifier of the newly linked domain. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.hvc.Links.
        Throws:
        AlreadyExists - If the link already exists.
        InvalidArgument - If the values of any of the properties of the spec parameter are not valid.
        Unsupported - If the PSC or the VC version is not supported.
        Unauthorized - If the user is not authorized.
        UnverifiedPeer - If the SSL certificate of the foreign PSC cannot be validated by comparing with the thumbprint/certificate provided in CreateSpec#sslThumbprint/CreateSpec#sslCertificate or if CreateSpec#sslThumbprint/CreateSpec#sslCertificate is null. The value of the UnverifiedPeer#data) property will be a class that contains one of the properties defined in {@link com.vmware.vcenter.hvc.LinksTypes.CertificateInfo}.
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires HLM.Manage.
